{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-bdba8f373c39b7f6","input":{"filename":"pr_triage_action_report.md","title":"PR Triage Reviewer Action Report","markdown":"# PR Triage Reviewer Prioritized Action Report\n\n**Evidence**\n- Dossier loaded for agent 11‑pr‑triage‑reviewer.\n- Operational records analyzed (3 items, total risk 18, opportunity 9.5).\n\n## 1. Immediate Action – Record **11‑A**\n- **Title:** PR triage reviewer priority case\n- **Status:** urgent\n- **Impact:** 45,487 (highest)\n- **Risk Score:** 7 (high)\n- **Summary:** Core functionality (diff summarization, risk labeling, reviewer suggestion) is critical for the PR pipeline.\n\n### Recommended Steps\n1. **Assign Lead Reviewer:** @lead‑engineer (or the team’s PR‑ops lead).\n2. **Validate Diff Summarization Logic:** Run unit tests on the diff‑parser module; add integration test covering large PRs (>1k lines).\n3. **Risk‑Label Accuracy Check:** Cross‑reference with historical PR risk classifications; target >90% concordance.\n4. **Reviewer Suggestion Engine:** Verify that the suggestion algorithm respects ownership and load‑balancing rules.\n5. **Deploy to Staging:** Push the updated triage workflow to a staging environment and monitor PR processing latency.\n\n*Rationale:* Addressing the highest‑impact, high‑risk item first prevents downstream bottlenecks in the review pipeline.\n\n---\n## 2. Unblocking Action – Record **11‑C**\n- **Title:** PR triage reviewer blocked follow‑up\n- **Status:** blocked\n- **Impact:** 20,321\n- **Risk Score:** 8 (very high) – blocked risk escalates if not resolved.\n\n### Blocking Factors (Assumed)\n- Dependency on external audit service.\n- Missing configuration for repository‑specific rules.\n\n### Recommended Steps\n1. **Identify Dependency Owner:** Reach out to the `audit‑service` team (via #infra‑audit Slack channel).\n2. **Provide Temporary Mock:** Implement a local mock of the audit API to allow continued development.\n3. **Complete Configuration:** Review `triage-config.yml` for missing repository patterns; add placeholders.\n4. **Schedule Sync Meeting:** 30‑minute sync with cross‑functional stakeholders to define definitive integration timeline.\n\n*Rationale:* Even though status is blocked, the risk score is the highest; unblocking prevents risk escalation.\n\n---\n## 3. Ongoing Review – Record **11‑B**\n- **Title:** PR triage reviewer routine queue item\n- **Status:** in_review\n- **Impact:** 10,243\n- **Risk Score:** 3 (low)\n\n### Recommended Steps\n1. **Continue Current Review:** Keep the assigned reviewer @engineer‑reviewer engaged.\n2. **Document Findings:** Capture any edge‑case behaviors for future improvement.\n3. **Prepare Post‑Release Checklist:** Ensure the changes are reflected in the README, crediting the Vercel PR triage template pattern as required.\n\n*Rationale:* Low‑risk, routine item can proceed in parallel while higher‑priority actions are underway.\n\n---\n## Summary & Next Actions\n| Priority | Record | Owner | Action Deadline |\n|----------|--------|-------|-----------------|\n| 1 | 11‑A | @lead‑engineer | 2 business days |\n| 2 | 11‑C | @infra‑audit lead | 3 business days (unblock) |\n| 3 | 11‑B | @engineer‑reviewer | Ongoing |\n\n**Assumptions**\n- Blocking factors for 11‑C are external service dependency and config gaps (inferred from the summary).\n- Reviewer availability aligns with current team assignments.\n- No secret or confidential information is required for these actions.\n\n**Next Steps**\n- Communicate the prioritized plan on the #pr‑triage channel.\n- Track progress via the engineering project board, marking each record as it moves to *Done*.\n\n*Report generated by PR Triage Reviewer (agent 11‑pr‑triage‑reviewer).*"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:09:30.586Z"}}
